column23: Established in 1978, Au Bon Pain is a restaurant and caf  chain that has more than 200 locations in the United States, South Korea, Taiwan and Thailand. Its menu includes a selection of sandwiches, breads, soups, salads, entrees, desserts and beverages. Au Bon Pain specializes in making artisan bread. The restaurant chain also offers a special menu for children that includes chicken nuggets, grilled chicken sandwiches and pasta. Au Bon Pain offers catering services for several occasions and has a team of consultants that assists its customers with menu selections and order processing. It caters events for corporations, cultural institutions, hospitals and nonprofit foundations. The restaurant chain additionally provides gift baskets that include a variety of food items, such as pastries, cookies, brownies, coffee and tea. It has also established a Food for Life program that provides food to poor families and individuals.

column23: The Cheesecake Factory operates a chain of casual dining restaurants and offers more than 200 menu selections. Apart from a range of different types of cheesecakes, the company offers a variety of appetizers, pizzas, pasta, seafood, steaks, salads and sandwiches. Its menu also features specialty dishes like chicken madeira, miso salmon, cajun jambalaya pasta and the factory burger. Founded in 1972, it serves over 50 cheesecakes and desserts, such as white chocolate raspberry truffle, Godiva chocolate, tres leches, fresh strawberry, fresh banana cream and kahlua cocoa coffee. The company s facilities feature French limestone floors and decorative columns, hand-painted fabrics, contemporary lighting and cherry wood d cor. Its restaurants provide lunch, dinner, late night dining, full bar and Sunday brunch services. The Cheesecake Factory also offers the entire menu for take-out. It operates a restaurant in Boston.

Costas Provisions, established in 1985, serves restaurant and institutional accounts, as well as operating a grovery, convenience food store, providing meat, poultry, snack foods and specialty and gourmet goods. Costas Provisions serves the Connecticut, Massachusetts and Rhode Island markets. Costa Provisions' charitable works include the canned goods hunger eradication programs, emergency food supply services and the World food program services. Costas Provisions is located in Boston.

CVS Pharmacy Inc. is one of the largest pharmacy retailers in the United States. The firm offers a range of hair, beauty, baby, lip, skin and ear care products. Some of its other products include soaps, vitamins, facial cleansers, body lotions and eye creams. The firm also renders an array of services, such as refill prescriptions, new prescriptions, drug corner and transfer prescriptions. CVS Pharmacy Inc. is a subsidiary of CVS Caremark Corporation, one of the largest pharmacy health care providers in the United States.

CVS/pharmacy is the retail division of CVS Caremark Corporation, which is one of the largest retail pharmacies in the United States with more than 6,200 retail locations. It serves the health care needs of customers and offers baby and child care, cosmetic, diet and nutrition, home medical and household items. CVS/pharmacy also provides natural, sexual health, skin care, personal and bath items, as well as medicines. CVS Caremark Corporation fills and manages more than 1 billion prescriptions annually and employs a staff of nearly 190,000 pharmacists and nurse practitioners. The corporation organizes a variety of retail loyalty programs and maintains pharmacy benefit management, mail order and specialty pharmacy divisions. Headquartered in Woonsocket, R.I., CVS/pharmacy maintains a store in Chestnut Hill, Mass.

CVS Caremark is one of the largest pharmacy health care providers in the United States. Based in Boston, Mass., the company offers pharmacy care through a wide range of services, including prescription refills, over-the-counter medications, automatic refills, round the clock/emergency services, insurance support and more. It also provides an array of products across various categories, such as beauty, baby and care, soaps, vitamins and many more. CVS Caremark operates as mail order pharmacy, retail pharmacy, specialty pharmacy and retail clinics. It is also a major provider of Medicare Part D Prescription Drug Plans.

DeLuca s Market operates multiple retail stores in Boston. Its stores offer a variety of grocery, bakery, deli, cheese, meat, and fruit and vegetable items. Its prepared food items include pork roast, steamed squash, steamed asparagus, baby brussel sprouts, saut ed salmon, eggplant Parmesan, baked potatoes, glazed shrimp kabobs, meatballs and honey-glazed sweet potato strips. Additionally, it offers stuffed mushrooms, quesadillas, baked potatoes and fish cakes. DeLuca s Market offers a variety of Italian pottery items that include wall plates, cups, saucers, vases, jars, pitchers and decanters. The market s locations also offer a variety of beer, spirits, and red and white wines.

In operation since 1950, Dunkin' Donuts is one of the largest coffee and baked-good chains in the world. Located in South Boston, Mass., the restaurant serves coffee, tea, donuts, bagels, deli, cookies and muffins, to name a few. It also offers biscuits, breakfast sandwiches, iced tea, flatbread sandwiches, white-hot chocolate, coolatta, iced lattes, hot/iced coffee and flavored-iced coffee. Dunkin' Donuts is a subsidiary of Dunkin' Brands Inc. which operates more than 9,000 restaurants in 31 countries.

column23: Recognizing a potential niche producing fresh New York style bagels, the partners of Finagle A Bagel went to New York in 1989 to learn bagel baking. They returned to Boston with the desire to serve the best bagel in the region and founded the company in the Quincy Market Building of historic Faneuil Hall Marketplace. Since, Finagle A Bagel has grown into a popular location in the Boston area. The company is known for combining quality ingredients, variety and freshness in the form of a fresh baked jumbo-sized bagel. Its bagels are boiled, baked and cooled, then tumbled, still warm, into baskets for sale.

With a location in Boston, Foodie's Urban Market is a retail department store that features a selection of daily need items. The company serves neighborhood customers with a variety of foods and groceries. It offers vegetables, fruit , meat, cheese, cakes, cookies, muffins, donuts and salads, in addition to olive oil, vinegars, milk, pickles, potato chips, protein drinks and salt-free foods. It also provides specialty foods imported from Portugal and Italy, as well as a selection of Spanish cuisine. The company offers various wheat-free and whole grain packaged breads. Its specialty includes sandwiches and wraps. Foodie's Urban Market also offers prepared salami, spreads, chorizo, smoked fish and fresh pasta.

Golden Goose Markets Since 1978, our mission at the Golden Goose Market has been to provide the highest quality merchandise with fast, friendly service. We offer a full line of groceries, meat, seafood and produce, as well as a full service deli, pizza & prepared foods, gourmet specialties & cheeses and all your wine, beer, liquor and beverage needs. We are open from 6AM to 11PM, 365 days a year for your convenience. We offer free delivery throughout the North End, waterfront and downtown Boston. Please stop by and see us or call and we'll have your order ready when you get here or we'll deliver to your door. Whether it's a special occasion or complimenting a nice home cooked meal, having the right wine is essential. We have an excellent selection from which to choose and the staff on hand with the expertise to help you make your selection. We also carry beer ( domestic, imported as well as craft brewed ) and a full line of liquor choices. Whatever the occasion, The Golden Goose has you covered. Every day the Golden Goose Bakery offers an outstanding assortment of fresh bake delights, including a variety of muffins, cookies, breads and desserts. We also receive twice daily deliveries of local artisan breads and rolls. We have an excellent selection of imported and domestic gourmet cheeses cured meats olives and spreads. If you are planning a party, what better way to spice up your celebration than with a tray of specialty cheeses and cured meats from our gourmet cheese department. In addition, the gourmet department also carries a selection of fine chocolates, candies, nuts dried fruits and snack mixes.

J.Crew, founded in 1983, is one of the leading retailers of apparel, shoes and accessories in the United States. The company operates more than 200 retail stores and over 60 factory outlets. It provides products for men, women and children. The company offers shirts, sweaters, dresses, jackets, pants, shorts, skirts and bags. Its stores feature a variety of accessories, including belts, hats, scarves, socks and small leather goods. J.Crew provides jewelry items that include necklaces, lockets, bracelets and rings. The company offers products for special occasions, such as weddings and parties. Its products are available in a range of colors and sizes. J.Crew additionally offers gift cards of several denominations and provides shipping services.

Founded in 1990, Jamba Juice offers a variety of health beverages, juices and snacks. Its menu features various branded signature drinks, such as the Pomegranate Paradise, Peach Perfection, Strawberry Whirl, Mango Mantra, Tahiti Green Tea and Banana Berry. The store also offers catering, pickup and delivery services. Its specialty flavors include banana, chocolate, mango, orange, peach, peanut butter, pineapple, pomegranate and strawberry. Jamba Juice also provides special nondairy and nongluten products. Additionally, it supports various nonprofit organizations that promote physical activities for children. Jamba Juice, with a location in Boston, has more than 650 stores throughout the United States. It is owned and operated by Jamba Juice Company, which is a wholly owned subsidiary of Jamba.

column23: Legal Sea Foods is not just a restaurant selling fish, it is a fish company that is in the restaurant business. For more than 50 years, Legal Sea Foods has set the standard for quality and freshness in the restaurant business. Menu items include clam chowder, seafood gumbo, mussels, scampi, clambake, cioppino, tuna, artic char, salmon, swordfish, haddock, catfish, calamari, oysters, cherrystones, lobster and salads. In addition, the restaurant operates more than 30 family-owned restaurants from Boston to Florida and a mail-order business.

Legal Sea Foods is a seafood restaurant chain that owns and operates more than 30 restaurants along the East Coast. It is a family-owned company that has been operational for more than 50 years and maintains several locations in Boston. The restaurant chain s menu includes a selection of appetizers, entrees, desserts, soups, chowders and salads. It also serves raw oysters, smoked salmon, mussels, shrimp, sea scallops, Caesar salad, fried calamari and baked stuffed lobsters. Several restaurant locations have private dining rooms that hold up to 32 people and are available for various special occasions, such as family celebrations, rehearsal dinners and corporate business meetings. Legal Sea Foods offers a gluten-free menu that also includes food items for children. Additionally, it sells gift cards and offers full-service catering and event planning options.

column23: No Name Restaurant, Located in Boston, Mass., specializes in sea food plates. Established in 1917, the restaurant offers saut ed lobster with shrimps, scallops, broiled scrod, sole, smelts, shrimp saut , mussels, blue fish, salmon, scallops and sword fish, to name a few. It also serves seafood platter, lobster meat on a salad, shrimp on a salad, saute seafood with vegetables, steamed lobster, fried clams and scallops. In addition, No Name Restaurant offers scrod, fried-scrod sandwich, clam roll, grilled chicken on a salad, hamburger, cheeseburger, broiled-sirloin steak and boneless saute chicken.

Established in 1981, Panera Bread is one of the largest bread baking companies in the United States. Based in Boston, Mass., it features recipes that include bread pudding with apples, pecans and raisins, along with cinnamon raisin French toast, among others. The bakery also offers recipes in various categories, such as appetizers, breakfast and brunch, soups, salads and sides, sandwiches as well as desserts, to name a few. Its list of sandwiches include grilled sesame bagel with seared tuna, daikon sprouts and wasabi cream cheese, ham, gruyere and apple sandwiches on ciabatta, lucky new year's sandwiches with grapes, grilled camembert and pumpkin butter sandwiches, roasted red pepper and avocado sandwich, roast beef sandwiches with mustard sauce, grilled gruyere on asiago cheese bread and grilled turkey and brie sandwich with cranberries.

Panificio is a restaurant that offers a variety of Sicilian dishes for breakfast, brunch, lunch and dinner. It provides a range of salads, sandwiches, appetizers and entrees. The restaurant offers French toast, grilled chicken, turkey panini, tuna salad, stuffed zucchini and gnocchi Bolognese. Panificio also serves mussels, eggplant roulade, fettuccini, New York strip sirloin, and spaghetti and meatballs. It provides catering options for up to 500 people for various special events and private parties. The restaurant additionally provides a selection of homemade breads. Panificio s bakery items include pies, croissants, cakes and cookies. It offers various beverages, such as ice tea and flavored coffee.

column23: Quinzani's Bakery is a family owned and operated commercial bakery. It specializes in the production of sandwich rolls, dinner rolls and assorted French and Italian breads. Quinzani's Bakery has been doing business since 1918. It caters to restaurants, hotels, caterers, food-service companies, deli's, and sub shops. The company sells wholesale only. From its central location in Boston's South End, it operates five delivery routes with its own fleet of trucks, covering all of the greater Boston area, including suburbs. Its products are also delivered through its network of more than 30 independent distributors who cover the remainder of New England.

column23: In 1860, George C. Shaw opened his first store in Portland, Maine. For more than 140 years, Shaw's Supermarkets has been operating a chain of grocery stores that offers a variety of food products and services. It employs approximately 30,000 associates in Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, Rhode Island, Connecticut and Vermont. The company provides a variety of food items, such as olive oil, frozen entrees and pizzas, coffees and teas, cookies, soups and meat products. Its additional products include cough and cold medications, pain relievers, vitamins and personal care items. In addition, Shaw s provides artificial preservatives and additives, nutritional supplements, batteries, light bulbs, disposable cameras and household products. Shaw's Supermarkets maintains a presence in Boston.

The supermarkets offer a variety of bakery, seafood, meat, poultry and cooked food items. The store s bakery goods include breads, rolls, bagels, pastries, donuts, pies, cookies and cream cakes. Its seafood items include salmon, catfish and shrimp. Additionally, it offers a range of fresh fruit and vegetables that includes mangoes, peaches, pineapples, grapes, cherries, lemons, carrots, onions, radishes, cabbages and tomatoes. Shaw s Supermarkets have an in-store pharmacy that offers prescription filling and health screening services. Its house brands include Shaw s, equaline, essensia, Happy Tails and HomeLife. Shaw's Supermarkets maintains multiple locations in Boston.

Skipjack's is a restaurant group founded more than 10 years ago in Brookline, Mass. Its restaurants offer a range of appetizers that includes smoked salmon, crab cocktail, steamer clams, fried calamari, coconut shrimp, chicken wings and crab cakes. The group s restaurants also provide a variety of entrees that includes crusted salmon, fried sea bass, swordfish kabobs, grilled mahimahi, steamed Maine lobsters, marinated steak tips and barbecue scallops. Additionally, its restaurants provide a range of salads that includes Caesar, Mediterranean and Cobb varieties. Skipjack's also provides its facilities for rent for organizing various private events. The restaurant group maintains a location in Boston.

After years of setting the standard for fine imported foods in the Boston area, Ihsan and Valerie opened South End Formaggio in Boston's historic South End in January of 1999. The space is smaller than our Cambridge store, but it has many of the same wonderful products packed into a cozy neighborhood shop. Together with our buyers at Formaggio Kitchen, we seek out the finest artisan products from Europe and North America. Our cheese and meat selection offers the fruits of these labors with many small production fermier and artisanal products from New England and further afield. Throughout our little store we pack in chocolates, olive oils, honeys, jams, and various other dry goods. We make the best of what space we have on our 'wine wall' to present an ecclectic selection of wines that we feel reflect the true nature of the grape, region and traditions that go into making the wine. Our artisanal beers are also seasonal and hand-selected. Finally, our kitchen makes fresh sandwiches, salads and dinner items daily from the best available local produce and naturally raised meats. Visit out store or shop online at www.formaggiokitchen.com, and stay updated with new products and discoveries by following us on Facebook and on our Formaggio Kitchen Cheese Blog. 268 Shawmut Ave, MA 02118 Boston 617-350-6996info southendformaggio.com

Trader Joe's is a privately held chain of specialty grocery stores headquartered in Monrovia, Calif. The company operates more than 280 stores in various cities throughout the United States, including Boston. Founded in 1958, Trader Joe s sells a variety of products, such as gourmet, organic, vegetarian, frozen and imported foods, as well as domestic and imported wines. Its alternative food items include breads, cereals, eggs and other products. Trader Joe s also offers nonfood items, including personal hygiene products, household cleaners, vitamins, pet food items, and plants and flowers. The company is also one of the exclusive retailers of Charles Shaw wine.

With more than 30 years, True World Foods, LLC has been one of the leading wholesale distributors of fresh and frozen seafood and specialty grocery items in North America. Based in Boston, Mass., the company has expertise in the wholesale seafood business. True World Foods LLC specializes in offering a variety of fresh tuna around the globe. The firm offers tuna species, such as Bigeye, yellowfin, southern bluefin and northern bluefin tuna. It caters to more than 8,000 restaurants, hotels, country clubs, retail markets, cruise ships and country clubs. The wholesale company offers a variety of non-seafood items, wagyu beef, dry grocery items, fresh produce as well as a full line of restaurant tools, supplies, service items and tableware.

Founded in 1901, Walgreens Co. is one of the leading drugstore chains in the United States that specializes in the business of pharmacy, providing health plans and health care solutions. The company operates more than 7,650 drugstores in the United States, District of Columbia and Puerto Rico. Based in Hyde Park, Mass., it provides multichannel access to approximately six million customers to consumer goods, pharmacy and health and wellness services. Walgreens business area covers sectors, such as retail, specialty, infusion, medical facility and mail service, as well as pharmacy benefit solutions and respiratory services. Fast Company has ranked Walgreen Co. among the top 10 companies in health care in 2010.

Incorporated in 1909, Walgreens Co., along with its subsidiaries, operates one of the largest drugstore chains in the United States. The firm specializes in selling prescription/non-prescription drugs and general merchandise, such as household products, convenience foods, personal/beauty care, candy, photofinishing and seasonal items. Located in Memphis, Tenn., some of its pharmacy services provided include retail, specialty, infusion, medical facility, long-term care and mail service. The firm operates nearly 8,046 locations across the United States, the District of Columbia and Puerto Rico.

Founded in 1980, Whole Foods Market is one of the world's leading retailers of natural and organic foods. With one of the stores located in Boston, it operates more than 190 stores in North America and the United Kingdom. The company employs more than 40,000 employees. Its subsidiaries include 365 Everyday Value, 365 Organic Everyday Value, Allegro Coffee Company, Animal Compassionate, Bread & Circus, and Fresh & Wild. Whole Foods Market's product categories include produce, seafood, grocery, meat and poultry, bakery products and prepared foods. Its specialty products include beer, wines and cheese, while its whole body category includes nutritional supplements; vitamins; body care and educational products, such as books; and floral, pet and household products. The company also sells a selection of products from conventional national brands.
